		</div><div id="linkcat-2563" class="side-widget widget_links"><h2>Most watched Film</h2>
	<ul class='xoxo blogroll'>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/a-bucket-of-blood/" title="Walter is a busboy overly impressed with the cool cats that hang out at The Yellow Door coffee house, and he wonders how to become “hip”">(1) A Bucket of Blood (1959)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/carnival-of-souls-1962/" title="After a traumatic accident, a woman becomes drawn to a mysterious abandoned carnival. Atmospheric 60s B-horror film with a cult following.">(2) Carnival of Souls (1962)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/city-of-the-deadhorror-hotel-1960/" title="College student Nan Barlow visits the village of Whitewood as research for her paper on witchcraft in New England, particularly the case of Elizabeth Selwyn. Her tutor, Professor Alan Driscoll(Lee), recommends the Raven’s Inn, run by a Mrs. Newless.">(3) City of the Dead/Horror Hotel (1960)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/the-mystery-of-the-leaping-fish-1916/" title="Coke Ennyday, the scientific detective, divides his own time in periods for “Sleep”, “Eat”, “Dope” and “Drink”. ">(4) The Mystery of the Leaping Fish (1916)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/this-is-a-test-taxi-rolling-stones-1981/" title="Coverage of Rolling Stones fans waiting for concert. The Stones perform Under My Thumb. Cab drivers share their stories of celebrity fares. Every famous person in the world gives better tips to cab drivers than Mick Jagger.">(5) This is a Test – Taxi, Rolling Stones (1981)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/night-of-the-living-dead-1968/" title="In this classic yet still creepy horror film, strangers hold up in a rural Pennsylvania farmhouse and battle constant attacks from dead locals who have been brought back to life by mysterious radiation.">(6) Night of the Living Dead (1968)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/white-zombie-1932/" title="A young man turns to a witch doctor to lure the woman he loves away from her fiance, but instead turns her into a zombie slave.">(7) White Zombie (1932)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/nosferatu-eine-symphonie-des-grauens-a-symphony-of-horror-1922/" title="– classic 1922 German Expressionist horror">(8) Nosferatu, eine Symphonie des Grauens (A Symphony of Horror) (1922)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/the-phantom-of-the-opera-1925/" title="A mad, disfigured composer seeks love with a lovely young opera singer.">(9) The Phantom of the Opera (1925)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch1design.com/blog/the-shopping-bag-lady-1975/" title="this film is the poignant story of a teenage girl’s encounter with a homeless old woman (movingly portrayed by distinguished actress Mildred Dunnock) who carries all her belongings around in shopping bags.">10. The Shopping Bag Lady (1975)</a></li>

	</ul>
